The Chronicle Wayne Chiridza, Showbiz Reporter Jah Prayzah and his 3rd Generation Band will this Saturday hold a show at Homestead Conference Centre in Bulawayo. The Dzamutsana hit maker who last performed in the city with Winky D seven months ago, will this time share the stage with Master Zhoe. The show will also feature a performance from the afro-sensation Mbeu and his band Mhodzi tribe who promise an action-packed night. Master Zhoe said he is excited about sharing the stage with Jah Prayzah who is renowned internationally. “This means a lot to perform with Jah Prayzah who is an established and respected musician internationally,” said Master Zhoe. He said he has been preparing well and cannot wait to give people a night of good music.—@waynecas